<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I asked Verant to modify the spell resistance for PvP combat - their reply</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:51 p.m. 19/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I asked Verant to modify the spell resistance for PvP combat - their reply<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Our concerns are being considered. There is hope for EQ PvP yet!
<BR>---------------------------------
<P>Geoffrey,
<P>I and my friends in the PvP Community will be holding our breath until then. I wish you
<BR>luck in getting the team to adopt changes such as this for PvP! Even if they are nothing
<BR>more than a crude hack, such as dividing the resistance factor in half if PvP level is within
<BR>4, this would be a vast improvement over the current state of affairs. We aren't asking for
<BR>perfection, just the rudiments of a workable system.
<P>Thanks again for taking our concerns to heart.
<P>The Black
<P>gzatkin@verant.com wrote:
<P>&gt;
<BR>&gt;Would it be possible to lessen the effects of spell resistance if the
<BR>&gt;casters target is another PvP player? Currently if you try to target
<BR>&gt;players just one or two levels above you, it is virtually impossible to
<BR>&gt;succeed. If spell resist was watered down in the 1-4 range of level
<BR>&gt;differences for PvP targets it would make an incredibly huge difference
<BR>&gt;in the PvP combat system! I hope you can help us.
<BR>&gt;
<P>Right now, casting on anything (player or monster) higher level than
<BR>you is harder - they save more often. I can see where it could cause
<BR>trouble in PvP - I'll bring it up in our tuning meeting.
<P>Geoffrey C. Zatkin
<P>Arch-Magi of Norrath
<BR>___________________________________________
<BR>____________________________________
